    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`plt.xticks()` not only sets the xticks labels, but also the positions. So you are in full control. In case you only want to change the xtick lables and not the positions you can use `set_xticklabels()`\n\n``` python\n>>> ax = df.plot(kind=\"bar\",stacked=False, use_index=False)\n>>> ax.set_xticklabels(df.index.get_level_values(\"RPT_Date\"))\n```\n"
