    "body": "> ax = df.plot(kind=\"bar\",stacked=False, use_index=False)\r\n> ax.set_xticklabels(df.index.get_level_values(\"RPT_Date\"))\r\n\r\n@lodagro If I want to reset the x ticks in a figure with multiple plots, how could I do this? I use ``for`` to create the plot and cannot get returned ``ax``. The only thing I could do is saving the returned value from ``df.plot`` everytime.\r\n````\r\nd = pd.DataFrame(cumsum)\r\nfor solver in solvers:\r\n\tindex = solvers.index(solver)\r\n\tax = d[solver].plot(color=colors[index], marker=markers[index], markersize=4)\r\n        ax.setxticklabels(xticks)\r\n````\r\nIs there other way to solve this problem? Another similar problem is in the comments [here](https://stackoverflow.com/a/9838032/6829195)\r\n\r\n"
